+# PAPER-CODE-VALIDATION-01 Countdown Repair Application Record
+
+**Date:** 2026-07-21
+**Claim:** `PAPER-CODE-VALIDATION-01`
+**Experiment:** `EXT-C-E8-TAPER-0.5B-01`
+**Base commit:** `147e26c7e63eefcf7feae24ae4b91b40a6bba1ef`
+**Scientific-status impact:** none
+
+## Applied engineering repair
+
+The Countdown reviewer runtime now explicitly releases caller-owned calibration,
+method-training, and saved-checkpoint model references before Python garbage
+collection and optional CUDA cache clearing. A weak-reference regression verifies
+that each cyclic fake model is collected before the next model load.
+
+The repair changes no objective, remoteness coordinate, method, coefficient,
+seed, dataset size, optimizer, scheduler, training budget, checkpoint rule,
+evaluation metric, scientific status, or manuscript value.
+
+## Validation completed before delivery
+
+- base file blob identities matched the canonical branch;
+- `git apply --check` passed;
+- repaired full files matched the validated after-images byte-for-byte;
+- Python compilation passed;
+- shared reviewer tests passed: 46 tests;
+- public CLI tests passed: 9 tests;
+- C-U1 package tests passed: 2 tests;
+- D-U1 CLI and public tests passed: 1 + 1 tests;
+- all public CLI help entry points passed;
+- the final reviewer-package boundary audit passed.
+
+Ruff was unavailable in the isolated local runtime and is not claimed as locally
+executed. The normal exact-head PR workflow must run Ruff, formatting, packaging,
+and the cumulative package suite after this update is applied and pushed.
+
+## Remaining separate gates
+
+Real Qwen/PEFT/CUDA liveness, real GPU allocator behavior, interrupted-run
+optimizer/scheduler resume, registered scientific execution, terminal scientific
+review, and method ranking remain outside this engineering acceptance.
