+# PAPER-CODE-VALIDATION-01 Final Reviewer-Package Boundary Audit
+
+**Date:** 2026-07-21
+**Claim:** `PAPER-CODE-VALIDATION-01`
+**Scientific-status impact:** none
+
+## Decision
+
+**PASS for the candidate reviewer-facing package boundary.**
+
+The audit was executed on the independently verified reviewer artifact with the
+accepted D4RL detached-factor repair and the Countdown model-release repair
+overlaid. It verified:
+
+- no source import of the internal `drpo` runtime;
+- no checkpoints, model weights, result archives, artifact directories, or
+  symbolic links in the standalone package;
+- required implementations and entry points for shared controls, C-U1, D-U1
+  revision 4, Hopper E7-Q2, D4RL-9, and Countdown are present;
+- the dependency-light Countdown core imports neither Transformers nor PEFT;
+- all public CLI help entry points open successfully;
+- the package continues to separate task-performance collapse,
+  support/probability/variance boundaries, numerical failure, and unavailable
+  environments;
+- reviewer execution never upgrades scientific status or authorizes method
+  ranking.
+
+## Executed candidate tests
+
+- Python compile: passed;
+- shared self-contained tests: 46 passed;
+- public CLI tests: 9 passed;
+- C-U1 package tests: 2 passed;
+- D-U1 CLI tests: 1 passed;
+- D-U1 public tests: 1 passed;
+- public CLI help checks: passed;
+- static boundary inventory: 150 files, zero prohibited payloads, zero symlinks,
+  zero internal `drpo` imports, zero heavy-runtime imports in Countdown core.
+
+A single combined pytest invocation exceeded the local process time limit, so the
+same suite was completed in the groups listed above. Ruff was not installed in
+the local runtime and is not claimed as executed.
+
+## Interpretation boundary
+
+This is engineering correctness and delivery-boundary evidence. It is not real
+HDF5/MuJoCo liveness, real Qwen/CUDA liveness, convergence, scientific terminal
+audit, or cross-method ranking. Normal exact-head PR CI remains required after
+the update is applied to the canonical branch.
